### Theme 5 — Preview-deploy URL resolution

#### 5.1 — `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4-12` 🔴 Critical

```ts
4    const isDevelopment =
5      env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV !== "production" &&
6      env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV !== "preview";
7
8    // The app (lightfast.ai) — makes tRPC calls to platform
9    export const appUrl = withProject({
10     projectName: "lightfast-app",
11     defaultHost: isDevelopment ? "http://localhost:3024" : "https://lightfast.ai",
12   });
```

`appUrl` is consumed at `apps/platform/src/app/(trpc)/api/trpc/[trpc]/route.ts:11`:

```ts
10    // Only the app calls platform tRPC — appUrl resolves per environment via VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS
11    if (origin !== appUrl) {
```

**Confirmed broken in production right now (not theoretical).**

Verified via `vercel env pull --environment=preview` (CLI 51.7.0, authenticated as `lightfast` org) against both `lightfast-platform` and `lightfast-app`: **`VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS` is absent in preview AND production** on both projects. The pulled env files contain the standard `VERCEL_*` system vars but no `VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS` and no `VERCEL_PROJECT_PRODUCTION_*` keys. Vercel only injects VRP when the project is explicitly linked via the dashboard's *Related Projects* / Microfrontends feature, and that linkage has never been activated.

**Consequence**: every preview deployment of `lightfast-platform` is currently 403-ing every cross-origin tRPC call from `lightfast-app`'s preview. The route comment at line 10 (`// appUrl resolves per environment via VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS`) is aspirational; the env var has never been set.

**Ground truth on `withProject`** (read from `node_modules/.pnpm/@lightfastai+dev-proxy@0.1.24/.../dist/projects.js:23-44`):

```js
export function withProject({ projectName, defaultHost, env = process.env }) {
  const projects = relatedProjects({ env, noThrow: true });   // parses env.VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS (JSON)
  const project = projects.find(p => p.project.name === projectName);
  if (!project) return defaultHost;                            // ← VRP missing OR project not listed
  if (env.VERCEL_ENV === "preview") {
    const previewHost = project.preview.customEnvironment ?? project.preview.branch;
    if (previewHost) return `https://${previewHost}`;
  }
  if (env.VERCEL_ENV === "production") {
    if (project.production.alias) return `https://${project.production.alias}`;
    if (project.production.url) return `https://${project.production.url}`;
  }
  return defaultHost;
}
```

If VRP is absent OR `projectName` isn't in the parsed list, it returns `defaultHost` unchanged — **no warning, no throw**. `resolveProjectUrl` (used by `apps/www/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4`) is a different code path: it loads `microfrontends.json` and resolves a portless dev URL in `NODE_ENV=development`, falling back to `applications[name].development.fallback`. **It does not consult VRP either.**

**Migration introduction** — commit `f51668a81` *"Decouple local app URLs from related-projects"* (this PR) renamed `*/lib/related-projects.ts` → `*/lib/project-urls.ts` across `apps/app`, `apps/platform`, `apps/www`, `api/platform`, switching from `@vercel/related-projects`'s `withRelatedProject` to `@lightfastai/dev-proxy/projects`'s `withProject`. **Same `defaultHost` fallback semantics — the migration carried the latent bug forward intact, didn't introduce it.**

**Proposed fix — three parts**:

1. **Vercel dashboard (out-of-band)**: link `lightfast-app` ↔ `lightfast-platform` via Settings → Environment Variables → Connect a related project. This makes `withProject` work as the route comment claims. Required regardless of code changes — without it, no preview deploys of platform can reach app.

2. **Code change — fail loud, not silent** (in this PR):

```ts
// apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts (proposed)
import { withProject } from "@lightfastai/dev-proxy/projects";
import { env } from "~/env";

function resolveAppUrl(): string {
  if (env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV === "production") {
    return withProject({ projectName: "lightfast-app", defaultHost: "https://lightfast.ai" });
  }
  if (env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV === "preview") {
    const resolved = withProject({ projectName: "lightfast-app", defaultHost: "" });
    if (!resolved) {
      throw new Error(
        "VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS missing 'lightfast-app' on the platform preview deploy. " +
        "Link the projects in the Vercel dashboard (Settings → Related Projects)."
      );
    }
    return resolved;
  }
  return "http://localhost:3024";
}

export const appUrl = resolveAppUrl();
```

Throwing during module init surfaces the misconfig on first request rather than silently 403-ing every call. Pair with a tightened comment at `route.ts:10`:

```ts
// Only the app calls platform tRPC — appUrl is resolved at module init from
// VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS (preview/prod) or localhost:3024 (dev).
```

3. **Cross-app consolidation (P2 follow-up)**. Today the four files are inconsistent:

| File | Helper | `defaultHost` for preview |
|---|---|---|
| `apps/app/next.config.ts:25-30` | `withProject` | `lightfast-platform.vercel.app` |
| `apps/app/src/lib/project-urls.ts:7-12` | `withProject` | `lightfast-platform.vercel.app` |
| `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts:9-12` | `withProject` | `lightfast.ai` ← **the bug** |
| `apps/www/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4` | `resolveProjectUrl` | reads `microfrontends.json` |

Consolidate into a shared `@repo/project-urls` (or `vendor/project-urls`) exporting `appUrl` + `platformUrl` helpers that:
1. Take an env arg (`{ NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV, VERCEL_URL }`) for testability.
2. Throw on `preview` when VRP is missing the required project (no silent production-host fallback).
3. Use a single canonical production fallback per project.
4. Are imported uniformly by all four call sites.

This kills the duplication in CodeRabbit nitpick 6.3, kills the `withProject` vs `resolveProjectUrl` inconsistency, and centralizes the "fail loud on missing VRP" contract so the next dev can't reintroduce a wrong production fallback.

