**What `lightfast.localhost` is**: the `*.localhost` TLD (RFC 6761) resolves to loopback automatically on macOS/Linux/recent Windows — no `/etc/hosts` entry needed. `lightfast.dev.json` configures `@lightfastai/dev-proxy` (a Vercel Microfrontends-aware reverse proxy) to terminate **HTTPS on port 443** for `lightfast.localhost`, with auto-issued local certs, fronting local Next.js servers (app on 3024, www on 3030, platform on 4112). No plain-HTTP form, no port-suffixed form in normal flow.

**Proposed fix** — static allowlist with subdomain match (env-driven and signed-token alternatives both rejected as overkill):

```ts
// apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_lib/safe-redirect.ts (new file)
const ALLOWED_REDIRECT_HOSTS = ["lightfast.ai", "lightfast.localhost"] as const;

function isAllowedHost(hostname: string): boolean {
  const h = hostname.toLowerCase();
  return ALLOWED_REDIRECT_HOSTS.some(
    (allowed) => h === allowed || h.endsWith(`.${allowed}`)
  );
}

export function sanitizeRedirectUrl(value: unknown): string | null {
  if (typeof value !== "string") return null;
  const trimmed = value.trim();
  if (!trimmed) return null;

  // Same-origin path: starts with "/" but not "//" (protocol-relative) or "/\" (backslash trick)
  if (trimmed.startsWith("/") && !trimmed.startsWith("//") && !trimmed.startsWith("/\\")) {
    return trimmed;
  }

  // Absolute URL: must parse, must use http/https, must be on an allowlisted host
  try {
    const url = new URL(trimmed);
    if (url.protocol !== "https:" && url.protocol !== "http:") return null;
    // HTTP downgrade attack defence: only allow http on *.localhost
    if (url.protocol === "http:" && !url.hostname.endsWith("localhost")) return null;
    if (!isAllowedHost(url.hostname)) return null;
    return url.toString();
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}
```

Edge cases handled: protocol-relative (`//evil.com`), backslash trick (`/\evil.com`), `javascript:`/`data:` URLs (rejected by protocol check), uppercase host (`Lightfast.AI` — lowercased), HTTP downgrade against production (rejected — only `*.localhost` may be HTTP), worktree subdomain (`branch.lightfast.localhost` — accepted via `endsWith`).

Then in `sign-in.ts`:

```diff
