`MAIN_WINDOW_VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL` is a Vite/electron-forge build-time constant. Production builds substitute `undefined`; dev builds substitute a literal `"http://localhost:5173/"`. The chance of it being a malformed string is essentially zero. CodeRabbit's defensive try/catch is correct hygiene but the impact ceiling is "dev-only crash on a Vite misconfig that nobody has triggered".

**Proposed fix** (low priority, but cheap):

```diff
 function rendererDevServerOrigin(): string | null {
-  return MAIN_WINDOW_VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL
-    ? new URL(MAIN_WINDOW_VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL).origin
-    : null;
+  if (!MAIN_WINDOW_VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL) return null;
+  try {
+    return new URL(MAIN_WINDOW_VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL).origin;
+  } catch {
+    return null;
+  }
 }
```

#### 6.3 — `apps/app/next.config.ts:21-30` (nitpick)

`apps/app/next.config.ts` defines a local `platformUrl` while `apps/app/src/lib/project-urls.ts:7-12` already exports the same value. Drift risk if one updates without the other.

**Proposed fix** — import the shared helper:

```diff
- const isDevelopment =
-   env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV !== "production" &&
-   env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV !== "preview";
-
- const platformUrl = withProject({
-   projectName: "lightfast-platform",
-   defaultHost: isDevelopment
-     ? "http://localhost:4112"
-     : "https://lightfast-platform.vercel.app",
- });
+ import { platformUrl } from "./src/lib/project-urls";
```

(Keep the import group sorted; theme 1.1 covers the import order.)

#### 6.4 — `package.json:24-25, 32-34` (nitpick)

```json
"dev:inngest": "npx inngest-cli@latest dev",
"check": "npx ultracite@latest check",
"fix": "npx ultracite@latest fix",
"lint:ws": "pnpm dlx sherif@latest",
```

`@latest` bypasses the lockfile — every developer can get a different CLI version on the same commit.

**Proposed fix** — pin via `devDependencies`:

```diff
   "devDependencies": {
     "@biomejs/biome": "2.4.12",
     "@changesets/cli": "^2.31.0",
+    "inngest-cli": "<pinned-version>",
+    "sherif": "<pinned-version>",
     ...
-    "ultracite": "7.6.0",
+    "ultracite": "7.6.0"   // already pinned — script just needs to use it
   }
```

```diff
- "dev:inngest": "npx inngest-cli@latest dev",
+ "dev:inngest": "inngest-cli dev",
- "check": "npx ultracite@latest check",
+ "check": "ultracite check",
- "fix": "npx ultracite@latest fix",
+ "fix": "ultracite fix",
- "lint:ws": "pnpm dlx sherif@latest",
+ "lint:ws": "sherif",
```

`ultracite` is already in `devDependencies` at line 69 (pinned to `7.6.0`) — the script could already drop `npx ...@latest` today.

## Code References

GHAS:
- `scripts/with-desktop-env.mjs:77` — alert #99 `js/clear-text-logging`

CodeRabbit inline (14):
- `apps/app/next.config.ts:1-11` — Biome import order
- `apps/app/next.config.ts:21-30` — duplication nitpick
- `apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_actions/sign-in.test.ts:59-71` — missing assertion
- `apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_actions/sign-in.ts:11-14` — open-redirect blocker
- `apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_components/otp-island.tsx:85-101` (also 146-181, 220-229) — race blocker
- `apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_components/session-activator.tsx:14-17` (also 19-27, 62) — race blocker
- `apps/app/src/app/(auth)/sign-in/page.tsx:47-49` — formatter blocker
- `apps/desktop/src/main/index.ts:47-50` — URL parse warning
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer/index.html:40-117` — formatter
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/entry.tsx:19-32` — formatter
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/user-menu.tsx:15` — aria-label
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/user-menu.tsx:15-53` — Biome attribute order
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/styles.css:167-170` (+8 sibling blocks) — Biome property order
- `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4-12` — preview defaultHost critical
- `db/app/src/client.ts:42-46` — withLocalBatch atomicity critical
- (consumer) `api/app/src/router/org/org-api-keys.ts:228-234` — actual batch call site

CodeRabbit outside-diff (3):
- `api/app/package.json:55` — dead `postgres` dependency
- `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-not-allowed)/_components/client-auth-bridge.tsx:26-56` — race
- `apps/app/src/proxy.ts:14-24` — formatter blocker

CodeRabbit nitpicks (2):
- `package.json:24, 32, 33, 34` — `npx @latest` not pinned

## Architecture Documentation

**Vendor abstraction rule (CLAUDE.md line 56)**: `Vendor abstractions: Standalone re-exports of third-party SDKs. Never import @planetscale/* directly → use @vendor/db`.

The current `vendor/db/src/index.ts` only re-exports drizzle's SQL utilities (`and`, `eq`, `desc`, etc.) and `alias`. It does **not** expose driver constructors. So `db/app/src/client.ts` imports `@neondatabase/serverless`, `drizzle-orm/neon-http`, `drizzle-orm/postgres-js`, and `postgres` directly. This is a longstanding gap — fixing it is its own refactor (Theme 4 Option C).

**`@lightfastai/dev-proxy/projects` `withProject` vs `resolveProjectUrl`**:
- `withProject({ projectName, defaultHost })` — returns the resolved URL or `defaultHost` fallback. Used in `apps/app/next.config.ts:25`, `apps/app/src/lib/project-urls.ts:7`, `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts:9`.
- `resolveProjectUrl("name")` — returns `null` when VRP isn't set. Used in `apps/www/src/lib/project-urls.ts:4`.

The `defaultHost` fallback is the source of the Theme 5 bug — it conflates "production" with "preview".

**Auth one-shot effect pattern**: three components (`otp-island.tsx`, `session-activator.tsx`, `client-auth-bridge.tsx`) all latch a `useRef<boolean>` to prevent duplicate execution, but all three set the latch *before* the async work succeeds. Same fix shape applies to all three.

## Historical Context (from thoughts/)

- `thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-23-codex-vs-lightfast-desktop-production-gap.md` — desktop production-gap research; relevant to the desktop-side findings (renderer formatting, main/index.ts URL parsing).
- `thoughts/shared/plans/2026-04-23-desktop-pre-release-batch.md` — the implementation plan that produced this PR.
- `thoughts/shared/plans/2026-05-04-pr630-test-plan-execution.md` — the test plan for this PR (already on disk, untracked).
- `thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-25-desktop-signin-agent-browser-workaround.md` — desktop sign-in flow context, relevant to Theme 3 (the absolute-URL `redirect_url` requirement).

## Related Research

- `thoughts/shared/plans/2026-04-19-collapse-vendor-lib-to-nanoid.md` — vendor abstraction pattern.
- `thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-20-lightfast-2-barebones-rearchitecture-baseline.md` — broader architecture baseline.

## Open Questions

All three open questions were resolved via parallel agent investigation on 2026-05-05. Findings are folded into Themes 3, 4, and 5 above. Summary of what was learned:

1. **Theme 4 / `withLocalBatch`** — *Resolved.* Production neon-http `.batch()` **is atomic**: traced the wire protocol through `drizzle-orm/neon-http/session.js:117-133` → `@neondatabase/serverless@1.1.0/index.mjs:1280-1296` → single `POST` to `https://${host}/sql` with `Neon-Batch-Isolation-Level` header → PlanetScale's neon-compat endpoint wraps in real `BEGIN…COMMIT`. The `org-api-keys.ts:230` "atomic" comment is true in prod, false in local. `withLocalBatch` was introduced on this PR (commit `1d14f390d`) as expedient drift, not by design. Recommended fix: callback-shape `db.runBatch(fn)` API.
2. **Theme 5 / VRP config** — *Resolved.* `VERCEL_RELATED_PROJECTS` is **not configured** on either Vercel project. Verified via `vercel env pull --environment=preview` — VRP absent in preview AND production on both `lightfast-platform` and `lightfast-app`. **Every preview deployment is currently 403-ing every cross-origin tRPC call.** Migration commit `f51668a81` carried the latent bug forward verbatim from the deleted `@vercel/related-projects` setup. Fix needs both Vercel-dashboard linkage AND code change to throw-on-missing.
3. **Theme 3 / allowlist** — *Resolved.* Legitimate hosts are exactly `{ lightfast.ai, lightfast.localhost }`, with subdomain support for git-worktree dev variants. `lightfast.localhost` is HTTPS:443 only (terminated by `@lightfastai/dev-proxy`, configured in `lightfast.dev.json`). No preview deploy URLs ever appear in `redirect_url`. The `redirect_url` plumbing through `initiateSignIn` was introduced on this PR (commit `ccafedc53`).

## Fix Priority (suggested)

### Out-of-band (user action, not code)

- **Vercel dashboard**: link `lightfast-app` ↔ `lightfast-platform` as Related Projects (Settings → Related Projects). Required regardless of code state — without it, no preview deploy of platform can reach app, and the throw-on-missing-VRP code change in Theme 5 will fire.

### Code changes

| Priority | Items | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **P0 (block merge)** | Theme 1 (CI failures), Theme 2.1, Theme 2.2, Theme 3.1, Theme 4.1, Theme 5.1 | Either CI is red, security, or confirmed production bug. |
| **P1 (this PR)** | Theme 2.3, Theme 3.2, Theme 4.2, Theme 6.3, Theme 6.4 | Same blast radius, low cost. |
| **P2 (follow-up PR)** | `@repo/project-urls` consolidation (Theme 5 cross-app), Theme 4.1 Option C (`vendor/db` refactor), Theme 6.1 (GHAS dismiss), Theme 6.2 (defensive try/catch) | Larger scope or low impact. |

### Implementation order within the P0 block

1. `pnpm fix` (clears Theme 1 — biggest noise reduction first).
2. Manual `aria-label` rename in `user-menu.tsx:15`.
3. Three auth race-condition patches (Themes 2.1 + 2.2 + 2.3 — same shape, batch them).
4. `safe-redirect.ts` helper + 3 call-site adoptions + tests (Theme 3.1 + 3.2).
5. `db.runBatch(fn)` rewrite + `org-api-keys.ts` migration + comment fix (Theme 4.1).
6. `apps/platform/src/lib/project-urls.ts` throw-on-missing-VRP + `route.ts:10` comment (Theme 5.1).
7. Drop dead `postgres` dep from `api/app/package.json` (Theme 4.2).
8. `apps/app/next.config.ts` import shared `platformUrl` (Theme 6.3).

